post_text:
Crystal City Schools are always looking for qualified substitute teachers. If you are looking for part time work and like working with kids fill out the application on our District page under 'Employment Opportunities' so we can get you on the list.
Individuals with valid Missouri teaching certificates who wish to substitute teach in a school district are no longer required by DESE to apply for a substitute certificate.
Please review the process from the DESE link.
https://dese.mo.gov/educator-quality/certification/substitute-teachers

Applications can be found on our website
http://www.crystal.k12.mo.us/employment_opportunities

Crystal City Elementary is planning to have a two week summer program that would run from July 20th-July 31st (7:30-3:00). Enrollment forms are DUE BY JUNE 15TH.

Our ability to provide this program will depend on the number of students participating and guidelines and direction from the health department.

Copies of the enrollment form can be printed from the attachment. If you need a paper copy we will also have copies in a folder, hanging on the front door of the elementary. The forms can be sent to gordons@crystal.k12.mo.us or turned in to the central office, in the high school building.

Notes from the Nurse-- May 2020

Please don‚Äôt skip your child‚Äôs wellness check-up!! Vaccinations are extremely important for your child‚Äôs health and the health of our community. No extensions or waivers are anticipated for next year‚Äôs immunization requirements so PLEASE do not put this off until the last minute. Students entering preschool, kindergarten, 8th grade, and 12th grade typically need immunizations. Your child must be up to date on immunizations to attend school (or have an exemption or in-progress card from a healthcare provider).

If your child has a chronic condition (asthma, food allergy, diabetes, etc) you will be receiving school action plans in the mail that need to be filled out by the healthcare provider before school starts. The forms will go out next week so be on the look-out.

Please feel free to email the nurse at richardsonamy@crystal.k12.mo.us with any questions about any of this information. Please continue to practice social distancing as much as possible and keep washing those hands! Stay safe and enjoy your summer!
text:
Notes from the Nurse-- May 2020

Please don‚Äôt skip your child‚Äôs wellness check-up!! Vaccinations are extremely important for your child‚Äôs health and the health of our community. No extensions or waivers are anticipated for next year‚Äôs immunization requirements so PLEASE do not put this off until the last minute. Students entering preschool, kindergarten, 8th grade, and 12th grade typically need immunizations. Your child must be up to date on immunizations to attend school (or have an exemption or in-progress card from a healthcare provider).

If your child has a chronic condition (asthma, food allergy, diabetes, etc) you will be receiving school action plans in the mail that need to be filled out by the healthcare provider before school starts. The forms will go out next week so be on the look-out.

Please feel free to email the nurse at richardsonamy@crystal.k12.mo.us with any questions about any of this information. Please continue to practice social distancing as much as possible and keep washing those hands! Stay safe and enjoy your summer!

Hey there Crystal City Hornet families and teachers!! We miss our kiddos so much and we are dying to see them.... even if it is a drive by and wave! So, here‚Äôs the plan...
Crystal City teachers and staff will be meeting at Bank of Bloomsdale (staying quarantined in our own cars practicing social distancing) at 1:00 pm on Monday and we will form a staff caravan. We will drive around all the neighborhoods in our attendance area and honk and wave to our kiddos. Please let your kids know we want to see them on their porches and driveways waving as we go by. Help us share this if you can!
This is pending any state or county restrictions that they may be put in place before then. Thanks ‚ù§Ô∏è
